issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When running an infference session to make predictions on a dataset, the memory usage keeps increasing without limit. 

The model is a LightGBM binary classifier trained in python, converted to onnx and used for inference in C#.


**Urgency**
We would like to deal with this issue as soon as possible, it is currently blocking development, and due to the memory usage it is impossible for us to send the application to production stage. 

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): Window 10 64
- ONNX Runtime installed from (source or binary): binary
- ONNX Runtime version: 1.4.0 (Nuget package)
- Python version: 3.6.7 (Onnx version on python is 1.7)
- Visual Studio version (if applicable): VS Proffesional 2019 16.4.11
- GCC/Compiler version (if compiling from source):
- CUDA/cuDNN version:
- GPU model and memory:

**To Reproduce**

Using a lightgbm model converted to onnx with path ModelPath and number of features nFeatures, get predictions on nSamples random tensors:

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
           ` var rand = new Random();
            using (var session = new InferenceSession(ModelPath))
            {
                var bufferInput = new float[nFeatures];
                var tensorInput = new DenseTensor<float>(bufferInput, new int[] { 1, nFeatures });

                using (FixedBufferOnnxValue valueInput = FixedBufferOnnxValue.CreateFromTensor(tensorInput))
                {
                    var inputNames = new[] { "input" };
                    var inputValues = new[] { valueInput };

                    for (var i = 0; i < nSamples; i++)
                    {
                        var inputs = Enumerable.Range(0, nFeatures).Select(x => (float)rand.Next(20, 150)).ToArray();
                        inputs.CopyTo(bufferInput, 0);
                        var result = session.Run(inputNames, inputValues);
                    }
                }
            }`

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

**Expected behavior**
Flat memory usage, not increasing over time each time session.Run() is executed.

**Screenshots**
![grow](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43389604/94253575-cdcf2900-ff25-11ea-977f-c432dcaf38ad.JPG)


**Additional context**
Due to company restrictions, I can't freely share the trained model. But, the model is a binary classifier with 137 features, and it has been trained in python using lightgbm, model parameters are:

n_estimators=2000, 
num_leaves=6, 
max_depth=-1
min_child_samples=20, 
subsample=0.5, 
subsample_freq=5, 
colsample_bytree=0.75, 
reg_alpha=1, 
reg_lambda=4

I have tried several other models trained with the same data, but different configuration of parameters, and number of features, in case the issue was caused by model complexity. The same effect happens when using any of this models.

body:
@glutamatt
I agree that "too much memory used", one possible alternative is to utilize ORT C/C++ API where you are empowered to release anything no longer needed, or you could go with C# where one could force GC to collect unused, I have tested C# API on your model - as long as as disposing everything timely and call GC.collect(...), the mem is flat. 
Shared allocators could indeed help the case when there are a lot of common weights between sessions, worth trying at least.
